    "Bays are bounded by straight aisles on both sides, and departments are not allowed to span over multiple bays [20].",
    "The width of the bays is determined by the cumulated area demand of the facilities assigned to each one using the equation below [21].",
    "The Slicing Tree Structure (STS) decomposes irregular shapes into simpler rectangles, easing the layout process.",
    "It involves iteratively partitioning a larger rectangular area into smaller rectangles through horizontal and vertical cuts.",
    "This method aims to find an arrangement of smaller rectangles that optimises the given layout objective [22]."
